    "_postman_id": "fffdcf3d-d864-44f9-b3d5-97cc4fa716b0",
    "name": "Food Delivery API",
    "description": "StartFragment\n\nFood Delivery API collection includes requests that exercise a typical food-ordering backend running locally (`http://127.0.0.1:8000`). It’s organized as an end-to-end workflow you can use to manually test (or run as a collection) the main user journeys:\n\n- **Auth**: register, user login, and admin login to obtain access for protected endpoints.\n    \n- **Restaurants**: create restaurant resources (admin/setup step).\n    \n- **Menu**\n    \n    - **Categories**: create and list menu categories.\n        \n    - **Items**: create menu items (and related menu item creation requests).\n        \n- **Cart**: add items to a cart and view the current user’s cart.\n    \n- **Orders**: place an order, view the user’s orders, and update an order’s status (admin/restaurant side).\n    \n- **Misc / Unsorted**: utility requests like payment status and a standalone listing request.\n    \n\nUse this collection to validate core flows: **sign up → authenticate → browse/build menu → add to cart → place order → track/update order → check payment status**.\n\nEndFragment",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "52487963",
    "_collection_link": "https://go.postman.co/collection/52487963-fffdcf3d-d864-44f9-b3d5-97cc4fa716b0?source=collection_link"
  },
