            },
            "description": "## Purpose\nCreate a new user account.\n\nThis endpoint registers a user with email/username/phone and a password confirmation (`password2`). On success it returns the created user (without password fields).\n\n## Endpoint\n`http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/users/register/`\n\n## Method\n`POST`\n\n## Required headers\n- `Content-Type: application/json`\n- `Accept: application/json` (recommended)\n\n> Authentication: not required for registration.\n\n## Request body (JSON)\n| Field | Type | Required | Notes / Validation |\n|---|---|---:|---|\n| `email` | string | Yes | Must be a valid email format; typically must be unique. |\n| `username` | string | Yes | Typically must be unique; allowed characters depend on server validation. |\n| `phone` | string | Yes | Expected as a string (e.g., digits). Validation depends on server rules. |\n| `password` | string | Yes | Must meet password policy enforced by the API (length/complexity, etc.). |\n| `password2` | string | Yes | **Must match** `password`. Used for confirmation. |\n\n## Example request\n```json\n{\"email\":\"test@gmail.com\",\"username\":\"testuser\",\"phone\":\"9999999999\",\"password\":\"Test@1234\",\"password2\":\"Test@1234\"}\n```\n\n## Success response\n### `201 Created`\n```json\n{\"id\":2,\"email\":\"test@gmail.com\",\"username\":\"testuser\",\"phone\":\"9999999999\"}\n```\n\n## Common error responses\n### `400 Bad Request` (validation)\nReturned when one or more fields are invalid or missing (for example, `password` and `password2` do not match, invalid email format, weak password, etc.). The response body typically contains field-level error messages.\n\n### `409 Conflict` (already exists)\nReturned when the user cannot be created because a unique field already exists (commonly `email` and/or `username`).\n\n## Local development notes\n- This request targets a local server at `127.0.0.1:8000`.\n- Ensure your backend is running locally (e.g., on port `8000`) before sending the request.\n- If your local base URL differs, consider using a variable such as `{{baseUrl}}` for easier switching between environments."
          },
