            "description": "## Purpose\nAuthenticate a user with email + password and receive JWT tokens.\n\n## Endpoint\n`POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/users/login/`\n\n## Method\n`POST`\n\n## Required body fields\nSend JSON in the request body.\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|---|---:|:---:|---|\n| `email` | string | Yes | User email address. |\n| `password` | string | Yes | User password. |\n\n## Example request\n```http\nPOST /api/users/login/ HTTP/1.1\nHost: 127.0.0.1:8000\nContent-Type: application/json\n\n{\"email\":\"test@gmail.com\",\"password\":\"Test@1234\"}\n```\n\n## Example 200 response\nOn success, returns a pair of tokens:\n- `access`: short-lived token used to access protected endpoints\n- `refresh`: longer-lived token used to obtain a new access token\n\n```json\n{\n  \"refresh\": \"<jwt_refresh_token>\",\n  \"access\": \"<jwt_access_token>\"\n}\n```\n\n## Common error responses\n> Exact status codes/messages depend on your API implementation.\n\n- **400 Bad Request**: Missing/invalid fields (e.g., malformed email, missing password).\n- **401 Unauthorized**: Invalid credentials (email/password incorrect) or account not allowed to authenticate.\n- **429 Too Many Requests** (if enabled): Too many login attempts / rate-limited.\n- **500 Internal Server Error**: Unexpected server-side error.\n\n## Notes: using the access token\nUse the `access` token as a Bearer token for authenticated requests:\n\n```http\nAuthorization: Bearer <jwt_access_token>\n```\n\nTypically, when the access token expires, use the `refresh` token with your refresh endpoint to obtain a new access token."
          },
